"""
Curated NCBI DNA Examples for NBDFinder Testing
===============================================

This module contains curated small DNA sequences from NCBI for testing and 
demonstration of NBDFinder motif detection capabilities. All sequences are 
from genes and small genomes as specified in the refactor requirements.

Accessions included:
- Human HBB (NG_000007.3) - Beta-globin gene cluster
- Human TP53 (NG_017013.2) - Tumor protein p53 gene
- E. coli K-12 fragment (U00096.3) - Representative bacterial genomic region
- Mycoplasma genitalium (L43967.2) - Small bacterial genome fragment
- HPV16 (NC_001526.4) - Human papillomavirus type 16 complete genome
- AAV2 (NC_001401.2) - Adeno-associated virus 2 complete genome

All sequences are DNA (not protein) and represent biologically relevant
regions known to contain various non-B DNA motifs.
"""

